OL,3,CInteractive map: Who controls my local
OL,4,Ccouncil?
OL,6,FLondon doesn't just have one council.
OL,7,FIt has 32 borough councils, plus the
OL,8,FCity of London Corporation which is
OL,9,Fover 1,000 years old and runs the
OL,10,Ffinancial district known as the Square
OL,11,FMile. On top of that, there is a
OL,12,FLondon-wide mayor.
OL,14,FLondon's 32 borough councils - from
OL,15,FBarnet in the north to Bromley in the
OL,16,Fsouth-east - are responsible for the
OL,17,Fservices you deal with most: rubbish
OL,18,Fcollection, local roads, libraries,
OL,19,Fsocial care, housing and most planning
OL,20,Fdecisions.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/5
