OL,3,CInteractive map: Who controls my local
OL,4,Ccouncil?
OL,6,FEvery borough is divided into smaller
OL,7,Felectoral wards where people vote to
OL,8,Fchoose one or more councillors to
OL,9,Fspeak for them on the local council.
OL,10,FWards are designed so that each one
OL,11,Fhas roughly similar numbers of voters,
OL,12,Fso representation is as fair as
OL,13,Fpossible.
OL,15,FCouncillors in London are elected
OL,16,Fevery four years. The party, or
OL,17,Findependent group, with the most
OL,18,Fcouncillors usually takes control and
OL,19,Fappoints a council leader.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/5
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
